31.title: The Fosters
31.plot: Jamie, a pretty but troubled young girl, is bounced around from orphanage to orphanage to juvenile detention facilities and back out onto the street. Her social worker is worried that Jamie is retreating deeper and deeper into herself, so she persuades a married couple who run a church program for troubled youths to take the girl in and try to bring her out of her shell. It turns out the couple has their own ideas on how to go about doing that.

32.title: Second Parents
32.plot: Young Sarah decides to bring along her friend Karen along for a holiday weekend with her mother and father. Karen is excited to go with what she believes to be the "perfect" family, but she soon realizes that Karen's parents' idea of "fun" isn't exactly what Karen told her it was.
